abstract: CBS News faced an ill-timed blow to its reputation on Wednesday following a bruising Democratic presidential debate that its moderators struggled to keep from spiraling out of control, although it could take some comfort in the numbers.
snippet: CBS News faced an ill-timed blow to its reputation on Wednesday following a bruising Democratic presidential debate that its moderators struggled to keep from spiraling out of control, although it could take some comfort in the numbers.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — CBS News faced an ill-timed blow to its reputation on Wednesday following a bruising Democratic presidential debate that its moderators struggled to keep from spiraling out of control, although it could take some comfort in the numbers.
headline_main: Rough Debate Performance by Moderators a Blow to CBS News
headline_print_headline: Rough Debate Performance by Moderators a Blow to CBS News

abstract: An employee opened fire Wednesday at one of the nation's largest breweries in Milwaukee, killing five fellow workers before taking his own life, police said.
snippet: An employee opened fire Wednesday at one of the nation's largest breweries in Milwaukee, killing five fellow workers before taking his own life, police said.
lead_paragraph: MILWAUKEE — An employee opened fire Wednesday at one of the nation's largest breweries in Milwaukee, killing five fellow workers before taking his own life, police said.
headline_main: Gunman Kills 5 at Milwaukee Brewery Before Taking Own Life
headline_print_headline: Gunman Kills 5 at Milwaukee Brewery Before Taking Own Life

abstract: Speaker Nancy Pelosi on Wednesday urged party unity amid Bernie Sanders' surge in the presidential race, even as House Democrats worry about a volatile election season that could put a self-described democratic socialist atop the ticket and threaten their majority.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Speaker Nancy Pelosi on Wednesday urged party unity amid Bernie Sanders' surge in the presidential race, even as House Democrats worry about a volatile election season that could put a self-described democratic socialist atop the ticket and threaten their majority.
headline_main: Pelosi Urges Democratic Unity Amid Sanders' Campaign Surge
headline_print_headline: Pelosi Urges Democratic Unity Amid Sanders' Campaign Surge

abstract: The lawsuit concerns an essay published a year ago and headlined “The Real Trump-Russia Quid Pro Quo.”
snippet: The lawsuit concerns an essay published a year ago and headlined “The Real Trump-Russia Quid Pro Quo.”
lead_paragraph: President Trump’s re-election campaign sued The New York Times for libel on Wednesday, alleging that an Op-Ed article published by the newspaper falsely asserted a “quid pro quo” between Russian officials and Mr. Trump’s 2016 campaign.

abstract: A local Hindu politician told the police to evict a group of Muslim protesters or he and his men would. Now, 25 have died in some of the worst violence in years.
snippet: A local Hindu politician told the police to evict a group of Muslim protesters or he and his men would. Now, 25 have died in some of the worst violence in years.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — To many in the eastern Delhi neighborhood where a convulsion of religious violence erupted this week, it all began with one man.

abstract: Flush with cash, President Donald Trump's campaign is stepping up its outreach to black Americans as it tries to claw away support from the traditionally Democratic voting bloc ahead of November's general election.
snippet: Flush with cash, President Donald Trump's campaign is stepping up its outreach to black Americans as it tries to claw away support from the traditionally Democratic voting bloc ahead of November's general election.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Flush with cash, President Donald Trump's campaign is stepping up its outreach to black Americans as it tries to claw away support from the traditionally Democratic voting bloc ahead of November's general election.
headline_main: Campaign to Open Trump Community Centers to Woo Black Voters
headline_print_headline: Campaign to Open Trump Community Centers to Woo Black Voters

abstract: The centers will register voters, sell campaign merchandise and promote policies that have benefited African-Americans, the campaign said.
snippet: The centers will register voters, sell campaign merchandise and promote policies that have benefited African-Americans, the campaign said.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In its latest attempt to win over African-American voters, President Trump’s 2020 campaign said Wednesday it would lease 15 retail properties in predominantly black neighborhoods across swing states like Florida and Pennsylvania, where it will build welcoming “community centers” that sell merchandise, register voters and spread the word about Trump policies that have helped black communities.

abstract: President Donald Trump's re-election campaign said on Wednesday it was filing a libel suit accusing the New York Times of intentionally publishing a false opinion article that suggested Russia and the campaign had an overarching deal in the 2016 U.S. election.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump's re-election campaign said on Wednesday it was filing a libel suit accusing the New York Times of intentionally publishing a false opinion article that suggested Russia and the campaign had an overarching deal in the 2016 U.S. election.
headline_main: Trump Campaign Says It Is Suing New York Times Over Russia Opinion Piece

abstract: Sixty-five years after 14-year-old Emmett Till was lynched in Mississippi, the House has approved legislation designating lynching as a hate crime under federal law.
snippet: Sixty-five years after 14-year-old Emmett Till was lynched in Mississippi, the House has approved legislation designating lynching as a hate crime under federal law.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Sixty-five years after 14-year-old Emmett Till was lynched in Mississippi, the House has approved legislation designating lynching as a hate crime under federal law.
headline_main: House Makes Lynching a Federal Crime, 65 Years After Till
headline_print_headline: House Makes Lynching a Federal Crime, 65 Years After Till

abstract: The Justice Department hailed the decision as a victory for public safety. Three other appeals courts had ruled against the administration on the issue.

lead_paragraph: The Trump administration can withhold millions of dollars from law enforcement agencies in states and cities that do not cooperate with U.S. immigration authorities, a federal appeals court ruled on Wednesday.
